            <p>06/07/06 18:36:19: Modified by studio@peptolab.com</p>

<p>Perhaps Zend_Table_Schema? I'd be wary of adding too much functionality to the base class. Perhaps the schema object could accept an instance of an existing table to :-</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$table = new myTable();

$schema = new Zend_Table_Schema($table);
$schema-&gt;addField('fieldname', array('type' =&gt; 'VARCHAR', 'null' =&gt; true));

$result = $table-&gt;fetchAll();
</code></pre>

<p>And you could use an instance of Zend_Config to import the structure. I would assume a more generic Zend_Config-type object would be passed for an 'exportStructure' method.</p>

<p>I think this would be a very useful addition as long as it's not too driver-specific. For instance, would you pass a generic string for field type, or create a more generic 'VARCHAR' property that can be translated into a specific database field type? That may make code more portable.</p>

